commentPostTextItems.html: Cermonies coming up soon
A superb performance by Australia, they have motored over Pakistan yet again, a win by 9 wickets
Pakistan batting was not up to the mark today to say the least
Ceremonies will be on the ground it seems as there was no crowd problem today
We are still waiting for the presentations
Lots of items to get through in the presentations
Momentos given to umps, officials and other staff
Momentos to Pak team and aus team in the form of medallions
Each player called up and receives a medal
an empty beer can thrown on and hits a player from the Pavilion balcony
Aussies go off
Waugh takes them off from in front of the pavilion
Bevan was hit on the cheeck, a shameful end unfortunately
They crowd is pretty far away, the can must have been thrown a long way
Now the crowd being pushed away, after spoiling the ceremony
Seems there is no way to find where it came from, could have hit anyone of the players
Ceremonies now moved indoors
In stark contrast, to the ugly incident, there are some people picnicing on the edge of the field
This commentary of the NatWest series was brought you by ECB.co.uk and cricinfo.com, please send any comments to comms@cricinfo.com
Next come the Ashes and please join us for live comms for this series
We are still waiting for the player ceremonies to find out the man of the match and other awards
Indoor presentations now
Momentos to the Aus team now starting off with the skipper then batting order
Man of the match, 76 off 93 balls, its Adam Gilchrist
Says he is pleased and a bit of deja vue too from the last world cup
Gold medal for man of the series, Waqar Younis
Says its a shame the end of the game today
Winning Trophy goes to Australia and Steve Waugh says we are pleased
THis was our best performance, we got it all together, regrets the incident at the end
Holds up the Trophy and calls over his players to share it
Thats all folk, see you soon for the Ashes, good night from Lord's
